						<summary>

						<p>The ends of lines of this inscription are lost. It seems to record a gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee every day in the temple of Tirumattirukkōyil-Perumāḷ at Śēṟṟūr by <hi rend="bold">Pāḷūraṉ Poṟṟā[marai] a maid-servant of</hi> he royal harem of <hi rend="bold">queen Kiḻānaḍigaḷ at Tanjavūr.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
